# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lesson 16 -- Content Understanding multimodal extractor  [KEYLESS]
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L16 is KEYLESS end to end -- there is NO key in this file. Auth flows
# through DefaultAzureCredential (az login); the signed-in user holds the
# "Cognitive Services User" role on the Foundry resource. The CU SDK builds
# the bearer token itself from that credential -- no key is ever read.
#
# One client, four modalities (lesson-16-extract.py routes by MIME type):
#   prebuilt-receipt     <- PDFs / documents (structured fields + confidence)
#                          (exam name: prebuilt-invoice; demo workaround as of mid-2026)
#   prebuilt-imageSearch <- images (one-paragraph description)
#   prebuilt-audioSearch <- audio (transcript + diarization + summary)
#   prebuilt-video       <- video (frames + transcript + shot boundaries)
#
# How to get these values:
#   1. Run Deploy-Lesson16-Infrastructure.ps1 (pass a unique -FoundryName).
#   2. Copy the printed output block here.
#   3. Never commit .env -- only .env.example.
#
#   CU_ENDPOINT:
#     The services.ai.azure.com endpoint the CU SDK expects (NOT the
#     cognitiveservices.azure.com form). The deploy script prints the
#     ready-to-paste value (it rewrites the endpoint form for you).
#     Example format: https://YOUR-RESOURCE-NAME.services.ai.azure.com/
#
# ONE-TIME SETUP (the deploy script reminds you):
#   CU prebuilt analyzers run on gpt-4.1 / gpt-4.1-mini /
#   text-embedding-3-large deployments you must map as the resource defaults
#   (sample_update_defaults.py or the Foundry portal Content Understanding
#   Settings blade). Until that mapping runs you will see:
#   "Default model deployment not configured".
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CU_ENDPOINT=https://YOUR-RESOURCE-NAME.services.ai.azure.com/
CU_API_VERSION=2025-11-01

# NEVER commit .env -- only .env.example.
